乳腺の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the compound, alveolar and apocrine accessory gland of the skin of mammals that secretes milk

definition.value: The neonatal male and female rat and mouse have 6 and 5 pairs of glands, respectively, with a single, central lactiferous duct, several branching secondary ducts, and numerous tertiary ducts (Ceriani 1970; Cardiff and Wellings 1999). In the rat, the glands are distributed in pairs along the milk line, with 1 pair cervical, 2 thoracic, 1 abdominal, and 2 inguinal (Astwood, Geschickter, and Rausch 1937). Distribution in the mouse is in the neck, chest wall (2 pairs), abdominal wall, and inguinal region (Cardiff and Wellings 1999).
